<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-23T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/11–2349:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_DLW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-23T16:00:00+00:00">November 23, 1949—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4669. Personal for the Secretary from <persName corresp="#p_DLW1">Douglas</persName>. ReDeptel 4124, November 15.<note n="1" xml:id="d143fn1">Same as telegram 4415, November 15, <ref target="#pg_316">p. 316</ref>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BE1">Bevin</persName> has asked me to deliver
                                the following personal message to you in reply to yours to him of
                                November 15:</p>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“It was most good of you to give me an account of your
                                    discussions with <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName>
                                    and <persName corresp="#p_SK1">Schumacher</persName> in Germany.
                                    As you know, I am following the situation with the greatest
                                    interest and was therefore particularly glad to get your
                                    message.</p>
                                <p>You will have seen that in my statement in Parliament I played
                                    Germany down as much as I could. I did not want to make it more
                                    difficult for Monsieur <persName corresp="#p_SR1">Schuman</persName>, but this made it politically difficult
                                    for myself.”</p>
                            </quote>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DLW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>